PUH v25 mechanical explanation The Cold Spot is the rebound throat void remnant — the depleted central region left after the shell collapse and bipolar jet eruption. Understandable: •  Rebound: Previous universe shell collapses to toroidal throat, jets blast matter/antimatter opposite poles. •  Throat center: Strands pulled outward → backwash depletion (low lattice density/tension). •  View: We look “down the muzzle” opposite matter jet → fewer early photons/ripples from depleted direction → colder, smoother patch. •  Size: Throat ~10 billion light-years projected angular scale matches ~6–10° today. •  Aligns dipole: Cold Spot opposite Shapley clump (jet endpoint).
